content:
The trip plan has been designed to meet all constraints, including the required stay durations, meeting/workshop windows, and direct flight connections. The itinerary ensures that flight days are shared between cities, meaning the day of the flight is counted for both the departure and arrival cities. The plan starts in Venice and ends in Mykonos, with all stays fitting within the 20-day period and respecting the flight connections.

The itinerary is as follows:
- Venice: Days 1-5 (5 days, including flight day to Edinburgh on Day 5)
- Edinburgh: Days 5-8 (4 days, including flight day from Venice on Day 5 and to Krakow on Day 8)
- Krakow: Days 8-11 (4 days, including flight day from Edinburgh on Day 8 and to Stuttgart on Day 11; meets friend between Days 8-11)
- Stuttgart: Days 11-13 (3 days, including flight day from Krakow on Day 11 and to Split on Day 13; workshop between Days 11-13)
- Split: Days 13-14 (2 days, including flight day from Stuttgart on Day 13 and to Athens on Day 14; meet friends between Days 13-14)
- Athens: Days 14-17 (4 days, including flight day from Split on Day 14 and to Mykonos on Day 17)
- Mykonos: Days 17-20 (4 days, including flight day from Athens on Day 17)

All direct flights used are supported by the given connections:
- Venice to Edinburgh (direct flight exists)
- Edinburgh to Krakow (direct flight exists)
- Krakow to Stuttgart (direct flight exists)
- Stuttgart to Split (direct flight exists)
- Split to Athens (direct flight exists)
- Athens to Mykonos (direct flight exists)

